"14:49:4" : {s: 14, a: 49, w: 4, r: "قرن", t: "مُّقَرَّنِينَ", l: "مُّقَرَّنِين", lc: 3, tl: "muqarranīna", lb: "বাঁধা, একত্রীকৃত",e: "bound together", b: "কষে বাঁধা", f: 2, rm: "to join one thing with another, couple. qarnin/qarnan - generation, century. qarn (dual qarnani, oblique qaraini, plu. qurun) - horn, trumpet. Often used to symbolise strength/power/glory. qarunun (pl. qurana) - mate, comrade, intimate companion. muqarranin - bound together. muqrinina - capable of subduing. muqtarinin - those formed in serried ranks, accompanying ones."},
